## Limitations

The analysis is limited by the availability of sources and the potential bias in historical interpretations. Many historical records were written by those who supported or benefited from slavery, which may skew the understanding of its impact. Additionally, the focus on U.S. slavery may overlook the global implications and variations of the institution in different regions.

